Closed / Target / Forecast

# calculate target by assuming proportions will remain constant
sales <- d %>% mutate(CloseDate = ymd(CloseDate)) %>% filter(year(CloseDate) > 
    2014, year(CloseDate) < year(today())) %>% group_by(month(CloseDate)) %>% 
    summarise(total = sum(Amount, na.rm = TRUE))

p <- sales$total/sum(sales$total)
target <- rep(32500000/12, 12) * p

# closed deals
d.sub <- d %>% mutate(CloseDate = ymd(CloseDate)) %>% filter(Owner.Name == params$Owner, 
    IsWon == "true", year(CloseDate) == year(today()), month(CloseDate) < month(today()) | 
        month(CloseDate) == month(today())) %>% group_by(month = month(CloseDate)) %>% 
    summarize(total = sum(Amount, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% arrange(month) %>% select(total)

closed <- c(d.sub$total, rep(NA, 12 - length(d.sub$total)))


# get forecasted deals
d.sub <- d %>% mutate(CloseDate = ymd(CloseDate)) %>% filter(Owner.Name == params$Owner, 
    IsWon == "false", IsClosed == "false", month(CloseDate) > month(today()), 
    year(CloseDate) == year(today())) %>% group_by(month = month(CloseDate)) %>% 
    summarize(total = sum(Amount, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% arrange(month) %>% select(month, 
    total)

forecasts <- data.frame(month = seq(1:12), total = rep(NA, 12))
forecasts <- forecasts[-d.sub$month, ]
forecasted <- rbind(forecasts, d.sub) %>% arrange(month) %>% select(total) %>% 
    as.matrix()


# assemble and plot the data

dates <- seq(mdy("1-1-2016"), mdy("12-31-2016"), by = "month")
x <- data.frame(Target = target, Closed = closed, Forecasted = forecasted)
D <- xts(x, order.by = dates)

dygraph(D, main = "Sales Data")

The ‘target’ category assumes the monthly proportion will be constant year over year and is based on a sales target of 3.25 million (expansion and renewals)

Company Sales Projection

# add a seasonally adjusted arima forecaset to closed deals
hist <- d %>% mutate(CloseDate = ymd(CloseDate)) %>% filter(year(CloseDate) > 
    2013, CloseDate < ymd(today()), IsWon == "true", IsClosed == "true") %>% 
    group_by(m = month(CloseDate), y = year(CloseDate)) %>% summarise(total = sum(Amount, 
    na.rm = TRUE)) %>% mutate(date = mdy(paste(m, "1", y, sep = "-")))

hist <- xts(hist$total, order.by = hist$date)
h <- as.matrix(hist)
fit <- Arima(hist, order = c(1, 1, 2), seasonal = list(order = c(1, 1, 2), period = 4))
fits <- as.matrix(fitted(fit))
f.length <- 12 - month(today())

f <- forecast(fit, h = f.length)

model <- c(fits, f$mean)
hist <- c(h, rep(NA, f.length))
h.length <- length(hist) - f.length
low <- c(rep(NA, h.length), f$lower[, "95%"])
upper <- c(rep(NA, h.length), f$upper[, "95%"])

x <- data.frame(Historical = hist, Model = model, Lower.95 = low, Upper.95 = upper)
dates <- seq(ymd("2014-01-01"), ymd(ceiling_date(today(), "year") - months(1)), 
    by = "months")

D <- xts(x, order.by = dates)
dygraph(D, main = "Total Sales: Historical and Forecast") %>% dySeries("Historical", 
    color = "blue") %>% dySeries(c("Lower.95", "Model", "Upper.95"), color = "green")

# annual cummulative sales
D.cum <- D %>% as.data.frame() %>% mutate(Date = ymd(rownames(.))) %>% filter(year(Date) == 
    year(today())) %>% select(Historical, Model, Date)
D.cum[is.na(D.cum)] <- 0
D.cum$Historical <- cumsum(D.cum$Historical)/1000000
D.cum$Historical[(12 - f.length + 1):12] <- NA
D.cum$Model <- cumsum(D.cum$Model)/1000000

D.cum <- xts(x = D.cum[, c("Historical", "Model")], order.by = D.cum$Date)

dygraph(D.cum, main = "Annual Cummulative Sales ($mils)") %>% dySeries("Historical", 
    color = "blue", stepPlot = TRUE, fillGraph = TRUE) %>% dySeries("Model", 
    color = "green", stepPlot = TRUE, fillGraph = TRUE)

‘Model’ refers to a seasonally adjusted ARIMA model. The seasonal adjustment is done by quarter, the model paramteres are 1,1,2.

Year

d.sub <- d %>% mutate(CloseDate = ymd(CloseDate)) %>% filter(Owner.Name == params$Owner, 
    IsWon == "false", IsClosed == "true", year(CloseDate) == year(today()), 
    Type == "Renewal") %>% mutate(month = month(CloseDate))

d.month <- d.sub %>% group_by(month) %>% summarise(total = sum(Amount, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
    arrange(month) %>% select(month, total)

if (nrow(d.month) > 0) {
    d.months <- data.frame(month = seq(1:max(d.month$month)), total = rep(0, 
        max(d.month$month)))
    d.months <- d.months[-d.month$month, ]
    
    d.months <- rbind(d.month, d.months) %>% arrange(month)
    
    ggplot(data = d.months, aes(x = month, y = total)) + geom_bar(stat = "identity")
} else {
    print("No Churn")
}

The total churn this year is 46181
